HEADWORD: Headstone
<hw>Head"stone`</hw> <pr>(-st⟦omac⟧n`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The principal stone in a foundation; the chief or corner
stone.</def> <rj><au>Ps. cxviii. 22.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The stone at the head of a grave.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Headstrong</ent>⟦br⟧
